Add this to the body of your html file:


<script type = "text/javascript">

        let scripts = [
            
            "script1",      
            "script2",
            "script3",

        ];
        
        for (i = 0; i < scripts.length; i++) {
            let script = document.createElement("script");
            script.setAttribute("type", "text/javascript");
            script.setAttribute("src", scripts[i] + ".js");
            document.head.appendChild(script);
        }
    </script>


replace script1, script2... with your own scripts. Its better to put them in order of dependence, the ones that depend on others lower on the list, for me it avoided class not found errors

Change the keycode in the Controller Class from 38(up) to 32(space), 16(shift) or 90(z).

      switch(key_code) {
  
        case 37: this.left.getInput(down);  break;
        case 38: this.up.getInput(down);    break;
        case 39: this.right.getInput(down);
  
      }
